## Definition
Actuaries use maths and statistics to help companies predict how much money they might need for financial risks, unexpected events, and future expenses.

## What the Job Involves
- Heavy use of Microsoft Excel; some coding
- Applying mathematical, statistical, and financial theories to analyse data
- Predicting financial risks
- Advising companies on how to prepare for future uncertainties

