## Education Pathway
**Minimum qualification:** Degree

| Stage | Degree Pathway (4–6 yrs) | Professional Certification Pathway (7–13 yrs) |
|-------|--------------------------|-----------------------------------------------|
| SPM | SPM | SPM |
| Pre-U | STPM / Asasi / Matriks / A-Levels / Foundation (1–2 yrs) | Same |
| Degree | Actuarial Science (3–4 yrs) | Any degree (3–4 yrs) |
| Certification | — | Actuarial Exams IFoA/SOA (3–7 yrs) |
| Entry Title | Actuarial Associate | Certified Actuary |

- Can enter without an Actuarial Science degree, but professional exams are required
- Actuarial Science graduates may receive exam exemptions

## Demand
High demand in insurance companies, consulting firms, and globally — especially post-certification.

## Expert Quotes
**Farhana (Actuary):** Role involves heavy Excel use and some coding to predict financial risks. Entry via degree + professional exams (IFoA/SOA) over 3–7 years while working.

**Anisha Puri (Actuary, Allianz Malaysia):** Certification allows you to become an Appointed Actuary with authority over financial decisions and regulatory approvals.

